    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.2/7–2646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Langdon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-26">26 July
                            1946</date>.<lb/>[Received July 26—5:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tfurc 56 [to Tokyo]. Following is a report of developments since our Tfurc 54 of
                    3 July.</p>
                <pb facs="0732" n="720" xml:id="pg_720"/>
                <p>Unity talks have progressed to the stage where both Right and Left have formally
                    appointed five delegates each to meet and substantiate unity. Rightist are Dr.
                    Kimm Kiu Sik, Won Sie Hoon,<note n="36" xml:id="d533fn1">Won Sai Hoon was
                        regarded as the actual head of the Democratic Party in south Korea.</note>
                    An Chai Hong,<note n="37" xml:id="d533fn2">An Chai Hong helped to found the
                        Nationalist Party after leaving the People’s Party because of its
                        radicalism.</note> Choi Tong Oh and Kim Boon Chun; Leftist are Lyuh Woon
                    Hyung, Hu Hun, Kim Wong Bong, Paik Nam Un and Lee Kang Kook. Choi is Chairman of
                    pool of mainly Rightist parties known as Emergency National Congress. Won is
                    Vice Chairman of Representative Democratic Council.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Langdon</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
